> Sure, we love figs baked into desserts, dried and nestled onto cheese platters, and preserved and slathered on toast for breakfast. But have you ever had them on your dinner plate? For this restaurant-worthy dish, we're mixing things up by pairing fig jam with tangy balsamic vinegar, plus sautéed shallot, butter, and beef stock. The result? A sweet and savory sauce that'll totally transform the seared steak it's drizzled over. And if a little of that sauce also touches the sides of roasted potatoes and almond-studded green beans, lucky you—it goes with everything!

Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and mince half the @Shallot{1} (all for 4 servings).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes} (you'll start the green beans after 15 minutes).

Meanwhile, toss @Green Beans{6%ounce} on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Once potatoes have roasted 15 minutes, place green beans on top rack. Roast until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While green beans roast, add @Sliced Almonds{1/2%ounce} to a large, dry pan over medium-high heat. Toast, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Pat @Sirloin Steak{14%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tablespoon} in pan used for almonds over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wash out pan.

Add a drizzle of oil and minced shallot to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Fig Jam{2%tablespoon}, and @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} and season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain. Divide between plates along with potatoes and green beans. Sprinkle green beans with toasted almonds, drizzle steak with pan sauce, and serve.